OL,3,CForced adoption survivors will receive
OL,4,C'full apology on behalf of the state'
OL,6,FThe government will make a "full
OL,7,Fapology on behalf of the state to all
OL,8,Fof those affected by historic forced
OL,9,Fadoption in England", Education
OL,10,FSecretary Bridget Phillipson has said.
OL,12,FAn estimated 185,000 children were
OL,13,Ftaken from unmarried mothers and
OL,14,Fadopted between 1949 and 1976 in
OL,15,FEngland and Wales.
OL,17,FAdministrations in Cardiff and
OL,18,FHolyrood have previously apologised to
OL,19,Fpeople affected, but campaigners have
OL,20,Flong called for an apology from the
OL,21,FWestminster government.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/4
