OL,3,CForced adoption survivors will receive
OL,4,C'full apology on behalf of the state'
OL,6,FIn the decades after Second World War
OL,7,Fan estimated 250,000 women had their
OL,8,Fchildren taken and adopted because
OL,9,Fthey were unmarried.
OL,11,FWomen claim their suffering, shame and
OL,12,Ftrauma have been ignored by successive
OL,13,Fgovernments.
OL,15,FPhillipson described the historical
OL,16,Fpractice as a "shameful period" in the
OL,17,Fcountry's history.
